        <h1 class="pt-5">Gran Turismo Franchise</h1>
        <p class="pb-4">Developed by Polyphony Digital, Gran Turismo is one of the most iconic racing series in gaming history, known for its realism, car variety, and PlayStation exclusivity.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="px-4 py-2">

        <h2 class="pt-4">Games in the Franchise</h2>
        <br />
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Gran Turismo (1997):</strong> The original PlayStation game that redefined racing games with simulation physics and a large car roster.</li>
            <li><strong>Gran Turismo 4 (2004):</strong> Widely regarded as one of the best entries, featuring a massive selection of cars and tracks.</li>
            <li><strong>Gran Turismo Sport (2017):</strong> A shift toward online racing and eSports with FIA support.</li>
            <li><strong>Gran Turismo 7 (2022):</strong> A return to the franchise's roots with single-player campaigns, tuning, and massive content depth.</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="my-4" />
        <div class="p-3 my-3" style="background-image: url('https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/Pu9kMvZZeGq2xhubY2MvN3.jpg'); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; ">
            <h2 class="pt-4">Key Features and Technologies</h2>
            <br />
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Photorealistic Graphics:</strong> Industry-leading visuals powered by PlayStation hardware, especially on PS5.</li>
                <li><strong>Driving Physics:</strong> Tuned for realism while remaining accessible to a wide audience.</li>
                <li><strong>Car Collection and Tuning:</strong> A deep garage system with customization, upgrades, and historic vehicles.</li>
                <li><strong>Music Rally & Scapes:</strong> Unique modes and photography systems not found in other sim racers.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-4" />

        <h2 class="pt-4">Target Audience</h2>
        <br />

        <p>
            Gran Turismo appeals to console racers of all skill levels. With its balance of accessibility and technical depth, it’s ideal for those looking to experience authentic racing without a complex PC setup.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-4" />

        <h2 class="pt-4">Community and Legacy</h2>
        <br />
        <p>
            As a PlayStation exclusive, Gran Turismo has cultivated a massive, loyal fanbase. From solo progression to FIA-endorsed events, it has played a key role in shaping console racing.
        </p>
        <p>
            The franchise continues to evolve with online features, competitive leagues, and a focus on realism that has stood the test of time.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-4" />

        <h2 class="pt-4">Gran Turismo Movie (2023)</h2>
        <br />
        <div class="p-3 my-3" style="background-image: url('https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w1280/7gFEPIcJDQvGq9xTvlPL2ZQB27c.jpg'); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; color: darkblue;">
            <p>
                Released in 2023, the <strong>Gran Turismo movie</strong> is a dramatized retelling of the true story of Jann Mardenborough, a young sim racer who transitioned from gaming to real-world motorsport through the GT Academy. Directed by Neill Blomkamp and starring Archie Madekwe, David Harbour, and Orlando Bloom, the film blends action, racing, and personal ambition in a way that highlights the real-world impact of the Gran Turismo series.
            </p>
